ight-wing political project of cow-protection, or examination of villagers' talk about bears who abduct women and have sex with them, Govindrajan illustrates that multispecies relatedness relies on both difference and ineffable affinity between animals.  Animal Intimacies breaks substantial new ground in animal studies, and Govindrajan's detailed portrait of the social, political and religious life of the region will be of interest to cultural anthropologists and scholars of South Asia as well.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aAnimalszIndiazUttarakhandxReligious aspects. 0aAnimals-India-Uttarakhand-Religious aspects. 0aHuman-animal relationshipszIndiazUttarakhand. 0aHuman-animal relationships-India-Uttarakhand. 0aWildlife conservationzIndiazUttarakhand. 0aWildlife conservation-India-Uttarakhand. 4aHimalayas. 4aHinduism. 4aSouth Asia. 4aagrarian studies. 4aconservation. 4aenvironmental anthropology. 4agender and sexuality. 4ahuman-animal relations. 4akinship. 4amultispecies ethnography. 70(DE-601)1042886120(DE-588)4078931-7aEthnologie2gnd 70(DE-601)1061409140(DE-588)4060087-7aTiere2gnd 70(DE-601)1062312860(DE-588)4038639-9aMensch2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226560045423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226560045.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles